  "prompt": "What are the legal precedents related to money laundering cases?",
  "response": "There are several important legal precedents related to money laundering cases. Some key examples include:\n\n1. United States v. BCCI Holdings (1991)\n- Landmark case involving massive international money laundering\n- Resulted in significant banking reforms\n\n2. Bank of Credit and Commerce International (BCCI) case\n- Major investigation revealing widespread financial crimes\n- Led to stricter international banking regulations\n\n3. US v. Levesque (2003)\n- Established guidelines for prosecuting money laundering\n- Defined specific intent requirements\n\n4. United States v. Santos (2008)\n- Supreme Court case clarifying money laundering statute interpretations\n- Addressed definition of \"proceeds\" in criminal contexts\n\n5. Basel Committee recommendations\n- International standards for anti-money laundering practices\n- Influenced global regulatory frameworks\n\nThese cases have shaped legal understanding and enforcement of money laundering statutes. However, I want to be transparent that while I can discuss general legal precedents, I recommend consulting legal professionals for specific detailed analysis.\n\nWould you be interested in hearing more about the general principles underlying money laundering legal precedents?",
